descp2: A `tf.dtype` identifies the type of labels. By default it is`tf.int64`. If user defines a `label_vocabulary`, this should be set as`tf.string`. `tf.float32` labels are only supported for binary classification.

A `tf.dtype` identifies the type of labels. By default it is`tf.int64`. If user defines a `label_vocabulary`, this should be set as`tf.string`. `tf.float32` labels are only supported for binary classification.
